Etymology . The specific epithet is a patronym for our good friend Dr. Colin Tilbury for his outstanding contributions to knowledge of African chameleons, most recently exemplified in his magnum opus , the Chameleons of Africa (
Tilbury 2010
). For the last 30 years his travels throughout Africa in search of chameleons, combined with his stunning photography, have been a source of inspiration. His studies have done much to enhance our understanding of African chameleons, and it is with great pleasure that we name this chameleon in his honour.
